text: Model Town (established in 1921) is a neighborhood and a union council (UC 127) in Lahore, Pakistan. The Model Town area is . It is divided into ten blocks (A,B,C,D,E,F,G,H,J,K) and seven extension blocks (L,M,N,P,Q,R,S). These are administered by Lahore Development Authority. The main places in Model Town includes the Bank Square Market, Model Town Park and Model Town Library. == References == Category:Towns in Lahore
title: Model Town Lahore
